:</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Submodule/Defs.html#Submodule\">Submodule</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">P</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Map a fractional ideal `I` to a submodule by forgetting that `∃ a, a I ⊆ R`.\n\nThis implements the coercion `FractionalIdeal S P → Submodule R P`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/FractionalIdeal/Basic.html#FractionalIdeal.coeToSubmodule","kind":"def","line":94,"name":"FractionalIdeal.coeToSubmodule","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/FractionalIdeal/Basic.lean#L94-L100"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/FractionalIdeal/Basic.html#FractionalIdeal\"><span class=\"name\">FractionalIdeal</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Submonoid/Defs.html#Submonoid\">Submonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">P</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2</div></div>","info":{"doc":"The fractional ideals of a domain `R` are ideals of `R` divided by some `a ∈ R`.\n\nMore precisely, let `P` be a localization of `R` at some submonoid `S`,\nthen a fractional ideal `I ⊆ P` is an `R`-submodule of `P`,\nsuch that there is an `a ∈ S` with `a I ⊆ R`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/FractionalIdeal/Basic.html#FractionalIdeal","kind":"def","line":76,"name":"FractionalIdeal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/FractionalIdeal/Basic.lean#L76-L83"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/FractionalIdeal/Basic.html#IsFractional\"><span class=\"name\">IsFractional</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Submonoid/Defs.html#Submonoid\">Submonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">P</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">P</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">I</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Submodule/Defs.html#Submodule\">Submodule</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">P</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A submodule `I` is a fractional ideal with respect to a submonoid `S`\nif `a I ⊆ R` for some `a ∈ S`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/FractionalIdeal/Basic.html#IsFractional","kind":"def","line":69,"name":"IsFractional","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/FractionalIdeal/Basic.lean#L69-L72"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.RingTheory.Localization.Integer","Mathlib.RingTheory.Localization.Submodule"],"instances":[{"className":"CoeOut","name":"FractionalIdeal.instCoeOutSubmodule","typeNames":["FractionalIdeal","Submodule"]},{"className":"SetLike","name":"FractionalIdeal.instSetLike","typeNames":["FractionalIdeal"]},{"className":"PartialOrder","name":"FractionalIdeal.instPartialOrder","typeNames":["FractionalIdeal"]},{"className":"Module","name":"FractionalIdeal.instModuleSubtypeMemSubmoduleCoeToSubmodule","typeNames":["Subtype"]},{"className":"CoeTC","name":"FractionalIdeal.instCoeTCIdeal","typeNames":["Ideal","FractionalIdeal"]},{"className":"Zero","name":"FractionalIdeal.instZero","typeNames":["FractionalIdeal"]},{"className":"Inhabited","name":"FractionalIdeal.instInhabited","typeNames":["FractionalIdeal"]},{"c